description:
Hello, we are currently seeking a skilled Angular Developer with a proven track record of building modern user interfaces using Angular and are passionate about creating seamless user experiences.

Responsibilities:

- Design, develop, and maintain user interfaces using Angular;
- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define project requirements;
- Ensure the performance, security, and scalability of web applications;
- Debug and resolve frontend defects and issues;
- Stay updated on the latest trends and technologies in Angular development;

Requirements:

- Proven experience as an Angular Developer with a strong portfolio;
- Proficiency in Angular and TypeScript;
- Experience with reactive programming and state management (RxJS, NgRx, etc.);
- Knowledge of backend technologies (Node.js, Express, etc.);
- Previous work on projects involving real-time updates;

Hello! We're seeking a talented Node.js Developer to join our team and drive backend innovation.

Responsibilities:

- Design and develop backend services and APIs using Node.js;
- Implement data processing and storage solutions using Node.js libraries;
- Optimize application performance and scalability;
- Collaborate with frontend developers to integrate frontend and backend components;
- Ensure code quality through testing and code reviews;

Requirements:

- Proven experience as a Node.js Developer with a strong portfolio of backend projects;
- Proficiency in JavaScript and Node.js framework;
- Experience with web frameworks like Express.js;
- Knowledge of SQL and NoSQL databases like MongoDB, PostgreSQL, or MySQL;
- Strong understanding of RESTful API design principles;

Nice-to-Have:

- Familiarity with frontend technologies like React.js;
- Experience with cloud platforms like AWS or Azure;
- Knowledge of containerization technologies like Docker;

How to Apply:

If you're excited about the opportunity to work on backend innovation using Node.js, please submit your proposal. Include details of your relevant experience, a link to your portfolio or GitHub, and your availability.
